184     /* Return all but the first "n" matched characters back to the input stream. */
185     #define yyless(n) \
186     	do \
187     		{ \
188     		/* Undo effects of setting up yyrubytext. */ \
189             int yyless_macro_arg = (n); \
190             YY_LESS_LINENO(yyless_macro_arg);\
191     		*yy_cp = (yy_hold_char); \
192     		YY_RESTORE_YY_MORE_OFFSET \
193     		(yy_c_buf_p) = yy_cp = yy_bp + yyless_macro_arg - YY_MORE_ADJ; \
194     		YY_DO_BEFORE_ACTION; /* set up yyrubytext again */ \
195     		} \
196     	while ( 0 )

205     #ifndef YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE
206     #define YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE
207     struct yy_buffer_state
208     	{
209     	FILE *yy_input_file;
210     
211     	char *yy_ch_buf;		/* input buffer */
212     	char *yy_buf_pos;		/* current position in input buffer */
213     
214     	/* Size of input buffer in bytes, not including room for EOB
215     	 * characters.
216     	 */
217     	yy_size_t yy_buf_size;
218     
219     	/* Number of characters read into yy_ch_buf, not including EOB
220     	 * characters.
221     	 */
222     	int yy_n_chars;
223     
224     	/* Whether we "own" the buffer - i.e., we know we created it,
225     	 * and can realloc() it to grow it, and should free() it to
226     	 * delete it.
227     	 */
228     	int yy_is_our_buffer;
229     
230     	/* Whether this is an "interactive" input source; if so, and
231     	 * if we're using stdio for input, then we want to use getc()
232     	 * instead of fread(), to make sure we stop fetching input after
233     	 * each newline.
234     	 */
235     	int yy_is_interactive;
236     
237     	/* Whether we're considered to be at the beginning of a line.
238     	 * If so, '^' rules will be active on the next match, otherwise
239     	 * not.
240     	 */
241     	int yy_at_bol;
242     
243         int yy_bs_lineno; /**< The line count. */
244         int yy_bs_column; /**< The column count. */
245         
246     	/* Whether to try to fill the input buffer when we reach the
247     	 * end of it.
248     	 */
249     	int yy_fill_buffer;
250     
251     	int yy_buffer_status;
252     
253     #define YY_BUFFER_NEW 0
254     #define YY_BUFFER_NORMAL 1
255     	/* When an EOF's been seen but there's still some text to process
256     	 * then we mark the buffer as YY_EOF_PENDING, to indicate that we
257     	 * shouldn't try reading from the input source any more.  We might
258     	 * still have a bunch of tokens to match, though, because of
259     	 * possible backing-up.
260     	 *
261     	 * When we actually see the EOF, we change the status to "new"
262     	 * (via yyrubyrestart()), so that the user can continue scanning by
263     	 * just pointing yyrubyin at a new input file.
264     	 */
265     #define YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING 2
266     
267     	};
268     #endif /* !YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE */

6056     /* yy_get_next_buffer - try to read in a new buffer
6057      *
6058      * Returns a code representing an action:
6059      *	EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH -
6060      *	EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN - continue scanning from current position
6061      *	EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE - end of file
6062      */
6063     static int yy_get_next_buffer (void)
6064     {
6065         	register char *dest = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf;
6066     	register char *source = (yytext_ptr);
6067     	register int number_to_move, i;
6068     	int ret_val;
6069     
6070     	if ( (yy_c_buf_p) > &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars) + 1] )

6073

6075     		{ /* Don't try to fill the buffer, so this is an EOF. */
6076     		if ( (yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr) - YY_MORE_ADJ == 1 )
6077     			{

6079     			 * treat this as a final EOF.
6080     			 */
6081     			return EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
6082     			}
6083     
6084     		else
6085     			{
6086     			/* We matched some text prior to the EOB, first
6087     			 * process it.
6088     			 */
6089     			return EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
6090     			}
6091     		}
6092     
6093     	/* Try to read more data. */
6094     
6095     	/* First move last chars to start of buffer. */
6096     	number_to_move = (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr)) - 1;
6097

6103     		 * just force an EOF

6105     		YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars) = 0;
6106     
6107     	else
6108     		{

6110     			YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
6111     
6112     		while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
6113     			{ /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */

6133     				}
6134     			else
6135     				/* Can't grow it, we don't own it. */
6136     				b->yy_ch_buf = 0;
6137     
6138     			if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
6139     				YY_FATAL_ERROR(
6140     				"fatal error - scanner input buffer overflow" );

6143     
6144     			num_to_read = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size -
6145     						number_to_move - 1;
6146

6148

6153     		YY_INPUT( (&YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move]),
6154     			(yy_n_chars), (size_t) num_to_read );

6192     	return ret_val;
6193     }

6217     /* yy_try_NUL_trans - try to make a transition on the NUL character
6218      *
6219      * synopsis
6220      *	next_state = yy_try_NUL_trans( current_state );
6221      */
6222         static yy_state_type yy_try_NUL_trans  (yy_state_type yy_current_state )
6223     {

6234     	if ( ! yy_is_jam )

6239     			(yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;

6271     
6272     		if ( yy_cp < YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
6273     			YY_FATAL_ERROR( "flex scanner push-back overflow" );
6274     		}
6275     
6276     	*--yy_cp = (char) c;
6277     
6278     	(yytext_ptr) = yy_bp;
6279     	(yy_hold_char) = *yy_cp;
6280     	(yy_c_buf_p) = yy_cp;
6281     }
6282     
6283     #ifndef YY_NO_INPUT
6284     #ifdef __cplusplus
6285         static int yyinput (void)
6286     #else
6287         static int input  (void)
6288     #endif
6289     
6290     {
6291     	int c;
6292         
6293     	*(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
6294     
6295     	if ( *(yy_c_buf_p) == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
6296     		{
6297     		/* yy_c_buf_p now points to the character we want to return.
6298     		 * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
6299     		 * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
6300     		 */
6301     		if ( (yy_c_buf_p) < &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)] )
6302     			/* This was really a NUL. */
6303     			*(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0';
6304     
6305     		else
6306     			{ /* need more input */
6307     			int offset = (yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr);
6308     			++(yy_c_buf_p);
6309     
6310     			switch ( yy_get_next_buffer(  ) )
6311     				{
6312     				case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
6313     					/* This happens because yy_g_n_b()
6314     					 * sees that we've accumulated a
6315     					 * token and flags that we need to
6316     					 * try matching the token before
6317     					 * proceeding.  But for input(),
6318     					 * there's no matching to consider.
6319     					 * So convert the EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH
6320     					 * to EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE.
6321     					 */
6322     
6323     					/* Reset buffer status. */
6324     					yyrubyrestart(yyrubyin );
6325     
6326     					/*FALLTHROUGH*/
6327     
6328     				case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:
6329     					{
6330     					if ( yyrubywrap( ) )
6331     						return EOF;
6332     
6333     					if ( ! (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) )
6334     						YY_NEW_FILE;
6335     #ifdef __cplusplus
6336     					return yyinput();
6337     #else
6338     					return input();
6339     #endif
6340     					}
6341     
6342     				case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
6343     					(yy_c_buf_p) = (yytext_ptr) + offset;
6344     					break;
6345     				}
6346     			}
6347     		}
6348     
6349     	c = *(unsigned char *) (yy_c_buf_p);	/* cast for 8-bit char's */
6350     	*(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0';	/* preserve yyrubytext */
6351     	(yy_hold_char) = *++(yy_c_buf_p);
6352     
6353     	YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_at_bol = (c == '\n');
6354     
6355     	return c;
6356     }
6357     #endif	/* ifndef YY_NO_INPUT */
6358     
6359     /** Immediately switch to a different input stream.
6360      * @param input_file A readable stream.
6361      * 
6362      * @note This function does not reset the start condition to @c INITIAL .
6363      */
6364         void yyrubyrestart  (FILE * input_file )
6365     {
6366         
6367     	if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ){
6368             yyrubyensure_buffer_stack ();
6369     		YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE =
6370                 yyruby_create_buffer(yyrubyin,YY_BUF_SIZE );
6371     	}
6372     
6373     	yyruby_init_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER,input_file );
6374     	yyruby_load_buffer_state( );
6375     }
6376     
6377     /** Switch to a different input buffer.
6378      * @param new_buffer The new input buffer.
6379      * 
6380      */
6381         void yyruby_switch_to_buffer  (YY_BUFFER_STATE  new_buffer )
6382     {
6383         
6384     	/* TODO. We should be able to replace this entire function body
6385     	 * with
6386     	 *		yyrubypop_buffer_state();
6387     	 *		yyrubypush_buffer_state(new_buffer);
6388          */
6389     	yyrubyensure_buffer_stack ();
6390     	if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER == new_buffer )
6391     		return;
6392     
6393     	if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
6394     		{
6395     		/* Flush out information for old buffer. */
6396     		*(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
6397     		YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
6398     		YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
6399     		}
6400     
6401     	YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
6402     	yyruby_load_buffer_state( );
6403     
6404     	/* We don't actually know whether we did this switch during
6405     	 * EOF (yyrubywrap()) processing, but the only time this flag
6406     	 * is looked at is after yyrubywrap() is called, so it's safe
6407     	 * to go ahead and always set it.
6408     	 */
6409     	(yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
6410     }
6411     
6412     static void yyruby_load_buffer_state  (void)
6413     {
6414         	(yy_n_chars) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars;
6415     	(yytext_ptr) = (yy_c_buf_p) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos;
6416     	yyrubyin = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_input_file;
6417     	(yy_hold_char) = *(yy_c_buf_p);
6418     }
6419     
6420     /** Allocate and initialize an input buffer state.
6421      * @param file A readable stream.
6422      * @param size The character buffer size in bytes. When in doubt, use @c YY_BUF_SIZE.
6423      * 
6424      * @return the allocated buffer state.
6425      */
6426         YY_BUFFER_STATE yyruby_create_buffer  (FILE * file, int  size )
6427     {
6428     	YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
6429         
6430     	b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyrubyalloc(sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state )  );
6431     	if ( ! b )
6432     		YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyruby_create_buffer()" );
6433     
6434     	b->yy_buf_size = size;
6435     
6436     	/* yy_ch_buf has to be 2 characters longer than the size given because
6437     	 * we need to put in 2 end-of-buffer characters.
6438     	 */
6439     	b->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyrubyalloc(b->yy_buf_size + 2  );
6440     	if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
6441     		YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyruby_create_buffer()" );
6442     
6443     	b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
6444     
6445     	yyruby_init_buffer(b,file );
6446     
6447     	return b;
6448     }
6449     
6450     /** Destroy the buffer.
6451      * @param b a buffer created with yyruby_create_buffer()
6452      * 
6453      */
6454         void yyruby_delete_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE  b )
6455     {
6456         
6457     	if ( ! b )
6458     		return;
6459     
6460     	if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ) /* Not sure if we should pop here. */
6461     		YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) 0;
6462     
6463     	if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
6464     		yyrubyfree((void *) b->yy_ch_buf  );
6465     
6466     	yyrubyfree((void *) b  );
6467     }
6468     
6469     #ifndef __cplusplus
6470     extern int isatty (int );
6471     #endif /* __cplusplus */
6472         
6473     /* Initializes or reinitializes a buffer.
6474      * This function is sometimes called more than once on the same buffer,
6475      * such as during a yyrubyrestart() or at EOF.
6476      */
6477         static void yyruby_init_buffer  (YY_BUFFER_STATE  b, FILE * file )
6478     
6479     {
6480     	int oerrno = errno;
6481         
6482     	yyruby_flush_buffer(b );
6483     
6484     	b->yy_input_file = file;
6485     	b->yy_fill_buffer = 1;
6486     
6487         /* If b is the current buffer, then yyruby_init_buffer was _probably_
6488          * called from yyrubyrestart() or through yy_get_next_buffer.
6489          * In that case, we don't want to reset the lineno or column.
6490          */
6491         if (b != YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
6492             b->yy_bs_lineno = 1;
6493             b->yy_bs_column = 0;
6494         }
6495     
6496             b->yy_is_interactive = file ? (isatty( fileno(file) ) > 0) : 0;
6497         
6498     	errno = oerrno;
6499     }
6500     
6501     /** Discard all buffered characters. On the next scan, YY_INPUT will be called.
6502      * @param b the buffer state to be flushed, usually @c YY_CURRENT_BUFFER.
6503      * 
6504      */
6505         void yyruby_flush_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE  b )
6506     {
6507         	if ( ! b )
6508     		return;
6509     
6510     	b->yy_n_chars = 0;
6511     
6512     	/* We always need two end-of-buffer characters.  The first causes
6513     	 * a transition to the end-of-buffer state.  The second causes
6514     	 * a jam in that state.
6515     	 */
6516     	b->yy_ch_buf[0] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
6517     	b->yy_ch_buf[1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
6518     
6519     	b->yy_buf_pos = &b->yy_ch_buf[0];
6520     
6521     	b->yy_at_bol = 1;
6522     	b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
6523     
6524     	if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
6525     		yyruby_load_buffer_state( );
6526     }
6527     
6528     /** Pushes the new state onto the stack. The new state becomes
6529      *  the current state. This function will allocate the stack
6530      *  if necessary.
6531      *  @param new_buffer The new state.
6532      *  
6533      */
6534     void yyrubypush_buffer_state (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
6535     {
6536         	if (new_buffer == NULL)
6537     		return;
6538     
6539     	yyrubyensure_buffer_stack();
6540     
6541     	/* This block is copied from yyruby_switch_to_buffer. */
6542     	if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
6543     		{
6544     		/* Flush out information for old buffer. */
6545     		*(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
6546     		YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
6547     		YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
6548     		}
6549     
6550     	/* Only push if top exists. Otherwise, replace top. */
6551     	if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
6552     		(yy_buffer_stack_top)++;
6553     	YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
6554     
6555     	/* copied from yyruby_switch_to_buffer. */
6556     	yyruby_load_buffer_state( );
6557     	(yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
6558     }
6559     
6560     /** Removes and deletes the top of the stack, if present.
6561      *  The next element becomes the new top.
6562      *  
6563      */
6564     void yyrubypop_buffer_state (void)
6565     {
6566         	if (!YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
6567     		return;
6568     
6569     	yyruby_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER );
6570     	YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
6571     	if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) > 0)
6572     		--(yy_buffer_stack_top);
6573     
6574     	if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER) {
6575     		yyruby_load_buffer_state( );
6576     		(yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
6577     	}
6578     }
6579     
6580     /* Allocates the stack if it does not exist.
6581      *  Guarantees space for at least one push.
6582      */
6583     static void yyrubyensure_buffer_stack (void)
6584     {
6585     	int num_to_alloc;
6586         
6587     	if (!(yy_buffer_stack)) {
6588     
6589     		/* First allocation is just for 2 elements, since we don't know if this
6590     		 * scanner will even need a stack. We use 2 instead of 1 to avoid an
6591     		 * immediate realloc on the next call.
6592              */
6593     		num_to_alloc = 1;
6594     		(yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyrubyalloc
6595     								(num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
6596     								);
6597     		if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
6598     			YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyrubyensure_buffer_stack()" );
6599     								  
6600     		memset((yy_buffer_stack), 0, num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
6601     				
6602     		(yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
6603     		(yy_buffer_stack_top) = 0;
6604     		return;
6605     	}
6606     
6607     	if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) >= ((yy_buffer_stack_max)) - 1){
6608     
6609     		/* Increase the buffer to prepare for a possible push. */
6610     		int grow_size = 8 /* arbitrary grow size */;
6611     
6612     		num_to_alloc = (yy_buffer_stack_max) + grow_size;
6613     		(yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyrubyrealloc
6614     								((yy_buffer_stack),
6615     								num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
6616     								);
6617     		if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
6618     			YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyrubyensure_buffer_stack()" );
6619     
6620     		/* zero only the new slots.*/
6621     		memset((yy_buffer_stack) + (yy_buffer_stack_max), 0, grow_size * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
6622     		(yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
6623     	}
6624     }
6625     
6626     /** Setup the input buffer state to scan directly from a user-specified character buffer.
6627      * @param base the character buffer
6628      * @param size the size in bytes of the character buffer
6629      * 
6630      * @return the newly allocated buffer state object. 
6631      */
6632     YY_BUFFER_STATE yyruby_scan_buffer  (char * base, yy_size_t  size )
6633     {
6634     	YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
6635         
6636     	if ( size < 2 ||
6637     	     base[size-2] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR ||
6638     	     base[size-1] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
6639     		/* They forgot to leave room for the EOB's. */
6640     		return 0;
6641     
6642     	b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyrubyalloc(sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state )  );
6643     	if ( ! b )
6644     		YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyruby_scan_buffer()" );
6645     
6646     	b->yy_buf_size = size - 2;	/* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
6647     	b->yy_buf_pos = b->yy_ch_buf = base;
6648     	b->yy_is_our_buffer = 0;
6649     	b->yy_input_file = 0;
6650     	b->yy_n_chars = b->yy_buf_size;
6651     	b->yy_is_interactive = 0;
6652     	b->yy_at_bol = 1;
6653     	b->yy_fill_buffer = 0;
6654     	b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
6655     
6656     	yyruby_switch_to_buffer(b  );
6657     
6658     	return b;
6659     }
6660     
6661     /** Setup the input buffer state to scan a string. The next call to yyrubylex() will
6662      * scan from a @e copy of @a str.
6663      * @param yystr a NUL-terminated string to scan
6664      * 
6665      * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
6666      * @note If you want to scan bytes that may contain NUL values, then use
6667      *       yyruby_scan_bytes() instead.
6668      */
6669     YY_BUFFER_STATE yyruby_scan_string (yyconst char * yystr )
6670     {
6671         
6672     	return yyruby_scan_bytes(yystr,strlen(yystr) );
6673     }
6674     
6675     /** Setup the input buffer state to scan the given bytes. The next call to yyrubylex() will
6676      * scan from a @e copy of @a bytes.
6677      * @param bytes the byte buffer to scan
6678      * @param len the number of bytes in the buffer pointed to by @a bytes.
6679      * 
6680      * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
6681      */
6682     YY_BUFFER_STATE yyruby_scan_bytes  (yyconst char * yybytes, int  _yybytes_len )
6683     {
6684     	YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
6685     	char *buf;
6686     	yy_size_t n;
6687     	int i;
6688         
6689     	/* Get memory for full buffer, including space for trailing EOB's. */
6690     	n = _yybytes_len + 2;
6691     	buf = (char *) yyrubyalloc(n  );
6692     	if ( ! buf )
6693     		YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyruby_scan_bytes()" );
6694     
6695     	for ( i = 0; i < _yybytes_len; ++i )
6696     		buf[i] = yybytes[i];
6697     
6698     	buf[_yybytes_len] = buf[_yybytes_len+1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
6699     
6700     	b = yyruby_scan_buffer(buf,n );
6701     	if ( ! b )
6702     		YY_FATAL_ERROR( "bad buffer in yyruby_scan_bytes()" );
6703     
6704     	/* It's okay to grow etc. this buffer, and we should throw it
6705     	 * away when we're done.
6706     	 */
6707     	b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
6708     
6709     	return b;
6710     }

6819     static int yy_init_globals (void)
6820     {
6821             /* Initialization is the same as for the non-reentrant scanner.
6822          * This function is called from yyrubylex_destroy(), so don't allocate here.
6823          */
6824     
6825         (yy_buffer_stack) = 0;
6826         (yy_buffer_stack_top) = 0;
6827         (yy_buffer_stack_max) = 0;
6828         (yy_c_buf_p) = (char *) 0;
6829         (yy_init) = 0;
6830         (yy_start) = 0;
6831     
6832     /* Defined in main.c */
6833     #ifdef YY_STDINIT
6834         yyrubyin = stdin;
6835         yyrubyout = stdout;
6836     #else
6837         yyrubyin = (FILE *) 0;
6838         yyrubyout = (FILE *) 0;
6839     #endif
6840     
6841         /* For future reference: Set errno on error, since we are called by
6842          * yyrubylex_init()
6843          */
6844         return 0;
6845     }
6846     
6847     /* yyrubylex_destroy is for both reentrant and non-reentrant scanners. */
6848     int yyrubylex_destroy  (void)
6849     {
6850         
6851         /* Pop the buffer stack, destroying each element. */
6852     	while(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
6853     		yyruby_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER  );
6854     		YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
6855     		yyrubypop_buffer_state();
6856     	}
6857     
6858     	/* Destroy the stack itself. */
6859     	yyrubyfree((yy_buffer_stack) );
6860     	(yy_buffer_stack) = NULL;
6861     
6862         /* Reset the globals. This is important in a non-reentrant scanner so the next time
6863          * yyrubylex() is called, initialization will occur. */
6864         yy_init_globals( );
6865     
6866         return 0;
6867     }

6898     void *yyrubyrealloc  (void * ptr, yy_size_t  size )
6899     {
6900     	/* The cast to (char *) in the following accommodates both
6901     	 * implementations that use char* generic pointers, and those
6902     	 * that use void* generic pointers.  It works with the latter
6903     	 * because both ANSI C and C++ allow castless assignment from
6904     	 * any pointer type to void*, and deal with argument conversions
6905     	 * as though doing an assignment.
6906     	 */
6907     	return (void *) realloc( (char *) ptr, size );
6908     }

6911     {
6912     	free( (char *) ptr );	/* see yyrubyrealloc() for (char *) cast */
6913     }

6927     static void
6928     count()
6929     {
6930             int i;
6931     
6932             if (rubylexreal_column != 0)
6933             {
6934               rubylex_column = rubylexreal_column+1;
6935             }
6936             for (i = 0; yyrubytext[i] != '\0'; i++)
6937             {
6938                     if (yyrubytext[i] == '\n')
6939                     {
6940                             rubylexreal_column = 0;
6941                             rubylex_column = 0;
6942                     } else if (yyrubytext[i] == '\t') {
6943                             rubylexreal_column += 8 - (rubylexreal_column % 8);
6944                     }else {
6945                             rubylexreal_column++;
6946                     }
6947             }
6948     }

6951     static
6952     void gobble_string(char which)
6953     {
6954     
6955       int bslash = 0;
6956       char c;
6957       while ((c = input()) && c != -1)
6958       {
6959     
6960         rubylexreal_column++;
6961         switch(c)  {
6962     
6963           case '\\':
6964                      if (!bslash)
6965                        bslash = 1;
6966                      else
6967                        bslash = 0;
6968                      break;
6969           case '\n':
6970                      rubylexreal_column = 0;
6971                      rubylex_column = 0;
6972                      rubylex_lineno++;
6973                      bslash = 0;
6974                      break;
6975           default:
6976                      if (c == which && !bslash)  {
6977                        return;
6978                      }
6979                      bslash = 0;
6980                      break;
6981         }
6982       }
6983     }

7025     static
7026     void ruby_accumulate_comment(char *data, int length)
7027     {
7028         int need = 0;
7029         char *  text = yyrubycomment;
7030     
7031         need = yyclength + length + 1;
7032         need = (need + 127) / 128 * 128;
7033         if (need > yyrubysize)
7034         {
7035             text = (char *)(yyrubysize ? realloc(yyrubycomment, need) : malloc(need));
7036             if (text == (char *)NULL)
7037                 return;
7038             yyrubysize = need;
7039             yyrubycomment = text;
7040         }
7041         memcpy(yyrubycomment + yyclength, data, length);
7042         yyclength += length;
7043         *(yyrubycomment + yyclength) = '\0';
7044     }

7046     static
7047     void reset_comment(void)
7048     {
7049         if (yyrubycomment != (char *)NULL)
7050             *yyrubycomment = '\0';
7051         yyclength = 0;
7052     }

7054     static
7055     int rubystyle_comment(void)
7056     {
7057         char    c;
7058         int i;
7059         int flag = 0;
7060     
7061         reset_comment();
7062         while ((c = input()) && c != -1)
7063         {
7064             rubylexreal_column++;
7065             ruby_accumulate_comment(&c, 1);
7066             if (c == '\n' || c == '\r')
7067             {
7068                 rubylexreal_column = 0;
7069                 rubylex_column = 0;
7070     
7071                 rubylex_lineno++;
7072             }
7073             while (c == '=')
7074             {
7075     			char tmp[4] = {0};
7076     			tmp[0] = '=';
7077     			
7078                 rubylexreal_column++;
7079                 
7080                 for (i = 1; i < 4; i++)
7081                 {
7082     				if (!(c = input()) || c == -1) {
7083     					return TOKEN_COMMENT;
7084     				}
7085     	            
7086     				if (c == '\n' || c == '\r')
7087     				{
7088     					rubylexreal_column = 0;
7089     					rubylex_column = 0;
7090     					rubylex_lineno++;
7091     				}
7092     				
7093     				if (c == '=')
7094     				{
7095     				    ruby_accumulate_comment(tmp, i);
7096     				    flag = 1;
7097     				    break;
7098     				}
7099     	            
7100     				tmp[i] = c;
7101                 }
7102                 
7103                 if (flag == 1)
7104                 {
7105     				flag = 0;
7106     				continue;
7107                 }
7108                 
7109                 if (!memcmp(tmp,"=end",sizeof(tmp)))  {
7110                     return TOKEN_COMMENT;
7111                 } else
7112                 {
7113                     ruby_accumulate_comment(tmp, sizeof(tmp));
7114                 }
7115             }
7116         }
7117         return TOKEN_COMMENT;
7118     }
